sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

%% ============================================================
%% SD Card Boot Sequence (with Load Addresses)
%% ------------------------------------------------------------
%% Scope:
%%    Describe how boot images are loaded from SD card
%%    into system memory before kernel execution.
%% Notes:
%% - MLO and U-Boot are vendor-provided (temporary)
%% - Addresses shown are typical for AM335x / BBB deployment
%% - This diagram describes deployment behavior, not OS design
%% ============================================================

    %% --- SYSTEM MEMORY DOMAIN ---
    box "AM335x System Memory" #f9f9f9
        participant ROM as Boot ROM<br/>(Silicon)
        participant SRAM as On-chip SRAM<br/>(64 KB)
        participant DDR as External DDR RAM
    end

    %% --- STORAGE DOMAIN ---
    participant SD as SD Card<br/>(FAT32)

    %% =========================================================
    %% Stage 1: Boot ROM
    %% =========================================================
    Note over ROM: Power-on Reset
    ROM->>SD: Scan boot sectors to locate<br/>first-stage bootloader (MLO)
    activate SD
    SD-->>SRAM: Load MLO into SRAM<br/>(0x402F0400)
    deactivate SD

    %% =========================================================
    %% Stage 2: SPL / MLO (Vendor)
    %% =========================================================
    Note over SRAM: SPL / MLO Execution<br/>(Vendor - Temporary)
    SRAM->>SRAM: Early hardware init<br/>(clock, basic setup)
    SRAM->>DDR: Initialize DDR controller

    SRAM->>SD: Load next boot stage image
    activate SD
    SD-->>DDR: Load U-Boot image<br/>(e.g. 0x8080_0000)
    deactivate SD

    %% =========================================================
    %% Stage 3: U-Boot (Vendor)
    %% =========================================================
    Note over DDR: U-Boot Execution<br/>(Vendor - Temporary)

    DDR->>SD: (Optional) Read uEnv.txt
    activate SD
    SD-->>DDR: Environment variables
    deactivate SD

    Note over DDR: uEnv.txt handling is vendor-specific

    DDR->>SD: Load kernel image (kernel.bin)
    activate SD
    SD-->>DDR: Place kernel at load address<br/>(0x8000_0000)
    deactivate SD

    %% =========================================================
    %% Stage 4: Control Handoff
    %% =========================================================
    Note over DDR: Control Transfer to Kernel
    DDR->>DDR: Execute go 0x8000_0000

    %% QUAN TRỌNG: Note phải viết trên 1 dòng
    Note left of DDR: CPU state at handoff:<br/>- SVC mode<br/>- MMU OFF<br/>- Cache OFF

    DDR->>DDR: Jump to kernel entry _start
    Note over DDR: Kernel execution begins